### How to set up a development environment (on Ubuntu 10.4)

Dependencies :
python >= 2.6
django >= 1.2
couchdb >= 0.11.0
coucdbkit >= 0.4.8

1. Install following packages:
python python-django python-couchdbkit couchdb git

You can install couchbkit via easy_install:
easy_install -U Couchdbkit

2. Create a Couchdb database called newebe (case sensitve) via Futon 
(http://localhost:5984/_utils).

3. Retrieve Newebe project:
git clone http://github.com/gelnior/newebe.git 

4. Change following constants in settings.py:
MEDIA_ROOT (path to your media directory).
TEMPLATE_DIRS (path to your template directory).

5. In Newebe directory run:
python manage.py syncdb

6. Then, still in Newebe directory run:
python manage.py runserver

7. In your browser, connect to http://localhost:8000/ and check that everything
is fine.

8. Run tests suite: 
python manage.py test platform news

### How to set up a production environment (on Ubuntu 10.4)

1. Follow steps 1 to 8 of development environment installation then stop 
django server.

2. Install Lighttpd server (make sure it does not conflict with other 
server installation like Apache).
apt-get install lighttpd

3. Add these lines to the end of your configuration file (/etc/lighttpd/lighttpd.conf) and change "/home/newebe/newebe" with you Newebe directory installation:

server.document-root = "/home/newebe/newebe"
fastcgi.server = ( "/newebe.fcgi" => ((
 "socket" => "/home/newebe/newebe/newebe.sock",
 "check-local" => "disable",
 )))

4. Set PROJDIR variable of start_newebe.sh file with you Newebe directory 
installation.

5. Run start_newebe script:
sh start_newebe.sh

6. In your browser, connect to http://localhost/ and check that everything
is fine.


